  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "EJ",
    "text": "This is a sketch I did in 1990, the way I remember the torture I experienced in 1944 in-- from the [NON-ENGLISH], the Hungarian Nazis internment took place. This is a sketch. I don't remember the exact date when I did it, but it's about the postcard which I received in 1941 from my mother in Budapest during the war. This is a photograph I did last year when I painted the portrait of Steven Spielberg. And I mailed it to-- I shipped it to him. And he sent me a, a nice letter-- a thank-you letter for-- he liked it very much. In this letter, he said that he liked the-- my, my portrait very much. This is the book called It's written in Hebrew and in English, which I have mentioned, during my interview, on which I based my project 'The Fifth Question.' In this book, it says, ask the fifth question during the ceremony of Passover.",
